direct_enhancements.reason: Both methods generate and validate Brazilian identification numbers (CPF and CNPJ) with similar logic and validation algorithms.
The cpf method relies on isCPFValid for validation, making it a direct dependency.
Both methods validate Brazilian identification numbers (CPF and CNPJ) using similar algorithms.
Both cpf and cnpj methods use calculateWeight for generating verification digits, making it a shared dependency.
Both cpf and cnpj methods use digit for calculating the final verification digit, making it a shared dependency.
Both isCPFValid and isCNPJValid methods use unmask to remove formatting, making it a shared dependency.
The cpf method uses cpf(String) from DocumentFormatterUtil to format the generated CPF number.
